cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.MM, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with congestion control and transport protocol extendability, which are core networking concepts. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of QUIC, which is a secure transport protocol. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possibility as the paper discusses the initialization of new connections and the utilization of available bandwidth, which are relevant to distributed systems. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possibility as the paper uses YouTube video chunks as an example and discusses the acceleration of video loading. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possibility as the paper aims to reduce flow completion time and increase efficiency.
